-- China to Sell 100,000 Tons of Sugar From Government Reserves, Website Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-28T02:14:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/china-to-sell-100-000-tons-of-sugar-from-government-reserves-website-says.html

          
          
             China will sell 100,000 metric tons
of sugar from state stockpiles on July 6, industry website
sugarinfo.net said today citing a joint statement from the
National Development and Reform Commission, the Ministry of
Commerce and the Mininstry of Finance. Minimum bids will be set
at 4,000 yuan a ton, it said.  
          
          


  


        